Police are hunting for two men suspected of murdering the Fakude family in Mpumalanga. The motive is still unknown. #eNCA reporterMasego Rahlaga is in the area. #DStv403 BUSHBUCKRIDGE - Mpumalanga police are searching for suspects involved in the brutal murder of a family of four near Bushbuckridge Tuesday night. Two suspects are believed to be involved. Neighbours say to have heard gunshots coming from the house of business owner Johnson Fakude around 7.30pm. READ:Â One of Mpumalanga's most wanted suspects arrested When police arrived, they found the bodies of Fakude, his wife, Gift Matsane and their two daughters Princess and Priscilla. The police have opened four cases of murder and are appealing for anyone with information to come forward. The motive is still unknown. Watch the video above for more details on this story.